{"abstract":[{"text":"Update your code to make use of the new ","type":"text"},{"code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"method on ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" which gives a succinct syntax for sending actions with case key paths, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":" method for overriding dependencies.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Sending test store actions","anchor":"Sending-test-store-actions","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.4 of the library introduced the ability to receive test store actions using case key path","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"syntax, massively simplifying how one asserts on actions received in a test:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["-store.receive(.child(.presented(.response(.success(\"Hello\")))))","+store.receive(\\.child.response.success)"],"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While version 1.6 of the library introduced the ability to assert against the payload of a received"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"action:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["store.receive(\\.child.presented.success, \"Hello\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.9 introduces similar affordances for "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sending"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" actions to test stores via"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore\/send(_:_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". These methods can significantly simplify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integration-style tests that send deeply-nested actions to child features, and provide symmetry to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how actions are received:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .destination(.presented(.record(.startButtonTapped))))))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.startButtonTapped)"," store.receive(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.timerTick)"]},{"type":"aside","style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Case key paths offer specialized syntax for many different action types."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s "},{"code":"presented","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" case can be collapsed:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.destination(.presented(.tap)))","+store.send(\\.destination.tap)"]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/IdentifiedAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be subscripted into:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .tap)))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].tap)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"And ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingAction","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"s can dynamically chain into a key path of state:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.binding(.set(\\.firstName, \"Blob\")))","+store.send(\\.binding.firstName, \"Blob\")"]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Together, these helpers can massively simplify asserting against nested actions:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(","-  .path(","-    .element(","-      id: 0,","-      action: .destination(","-        .presented(","-          .sheet(","-            .binding(","-              .set(\\.password, \"blobisawesome\")","-            )","-          )","-        )","-      )","-    )","-  )","-)","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.sheet.binding.password, \"blobisawesome\")"],"type":"codeListing"}],"name":"Tip"},{"text":"Overriding dependencies","level":3,"anchor":"Overriding-dependencies","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.2 of "},{"identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" introduced an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"alternative syntax for referencing a dependency:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["-@Dependency(\\.apiClient) var apiClient","+@Dependency(APIClient.self) var apiClient"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The primary benefit of this syntax is that you do not need to define a dedicated computed property","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"code":"DependencyValues","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which saves a small amount of boilerplate."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is now a similar API for overriding dependencies on a reducer, "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which can be used like so:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["MyFeature()","  .dependency(mockAPIClient)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The type of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mockAPIClient"},{"type":"text","text":" determines how the dependency is overridden."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This style of accessing and overriding dependencies is really only appropriate for dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"defined directly in your project. If you are shipping a dependency client that is used by others,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then still prefer adding a computed property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DependencyValues"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to be more discoverable."}]}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides